		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Jallianwala Bagh massacre</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>The <b>Jallianwala Bagh Massacre</b> (<a href="/wiki/Hindi" title="Hindi">Hindi</a>: जलियांवाला बाग़ हत्याकांड <i>Jallianwala Bāġa Hatyākāṇḍa</i>), alternatively known as the <b>Amritsar Massacre</b>, was named after the <a href="/wiki/Jallianwala_Bagh" title="Jallianwala Bagh">Jallianwala Bagh</a> (Garden) in the northern <a href="/wiki/India" title="India">Indian</a> city of <a href="/wiki/Amritsar" title="Amritsar">Amritsar</a> where, on <a href="/wiki/April_13" title="April 13">April 13</a>, <a href="/wiki/1919" title="1919">1919</a>, <a href="/wiki/British_Indian_Army" title="British Indian Army" class="mw-redirect">British Indian Army</a> soldiers under the command of Brigadier-General <a href="/wiki/Reginald_Dyer" title="Reginald Dyer">Reginald Dyer</a> opened fire on an unarmed gathering of men, women and children. The firing lasted about 10 minutes and 1650 rounds were fired, or 33 rounds per soldier. Official <a href="/wiki/British_Raj" title="British Raj">British Raj</a> sources placed the fatalities at 379. According to private sources there were over 1000 deaths, with more than 2000 wounded.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> Civil Surgeon Dr. Smith indicated that there were 1,526 <a href="/wiki/Casualty_(person)" title="Casualty (person)">casualties</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
